When Claude needs to call a tool, `stopreason` is `"tooluse"`, and the `content` array includes blocks of type `tool_use`:

```json
{
  "id": "msg_abc123",
  "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5",
  "stopreason": "tooluse",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tool_use",
      "id": "toolu_abc123",
      "name": "get_weather",
      "input": {
        "location": "北京"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Before a tool call, Claude may return a `text` block (e.g., “Let me check the weather”), or it may return a `tool_use` block directly, depending on the model’s judgment.

Claude can return multiple tool calls in a single response:

```json
{
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tool_use",
      "id": "toolu_1",
      "name": "get_weather",
      "input": { "location": "北京" }
    },
    {
      "type": "tool_use",
      "id": "toolu_2",
      "name": "get_weather",
      "input": { "location": "上海" }
    }
  ]
}
```

When returning results, you must provide a matching `tool_result` for each tool call:

```json
{
  "role": "user",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tool_result",
      "tooluseid": "toolu_1",
      "content": "{\"temperature\": \"25°C\"}"
    },
    {
      "type": "tool_result",
      "tooluseid": "toolu_2",
      "content": "{\"temperature\": \"28°C\"}"
    }
  ]
}
```

