The Responses API uses the `inputimage` and `inputfile` content types to handle multimodal inputs.

The Responses API currently supports image and PDF inputs only, and does not support audio or video. To process audio or video, use the Chat Completion API or the Vertex AI API.

```python [Python]
from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI(
    base_url="https://api.agipower.ai/v1",
    api_key="", # [!code highlight]
)

response = client.responses.create(
    model="openai/gpt-5", # [!code highlight]
    input=[
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "input_text",
                    "text": "Please analyze the content of the image."
                },
                {
                    "type": "input_image", # [!code highlight]
                    "imageurl": "https://cdn.marmot-cloud.com/storage/tbox-router/2025/08/05/e9445SU/shengchengtupian2025-04-09-1931.png" # [!code highlight]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
)

Extract the response
for item in response.output:
    if item.type == "message":
        for content in item.content:
            if content.type == "output_text":
                print(content.text)
```

