Model routing is easy to use—simply set the `model` parameter to `agipower/auto` and specify the candidate model pool via `modelroutingconfig`. If you do not specify `modelroutingconfig.available_models`, the system will use the platform’s full model pool.

Models on the AGIPower platform have unique slugs. You can get a model’s slug from the Models list page:
!model-slug
Or from the model detail page for a specific model:
!model-slug

```json [cURL Request]
{
  "model": "agipower/auto",
  "modelroutingconfig": {
    "available_models": [
      "anthropic/claude-4-sonnet", // Provide the model slug
      "openai/gpt-5",
      "google/gemini-2.5-flash-lite"
    ],
    "preference": "balanced"
  },
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Explain what quantum computing is"
    }
  ]
}
```

